  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Assistance to Populations Affected by Floods in Bujumbura Rural and Bujumbura Mairie, Burundi</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Burundi is facing a crisis that combines the devastating effects of natural disasters and deteriorating socio-economic and security situation in the country. It is located in an earthquake-prone geographic zone of the Great Lakes, which increases the risk of being affected by a catastrophic event. Frequent natural disasters such as floods and storms have provoked massive displacements of persons both in Bujumbura and in the provinces, and at an increasing rate; dangerous storms involving violent winds and torrential rains has also caused severe damage to property and populations, particularly in rural areas. The general objective of this project is to provide a comprehensive approach to address urgent shelter, water, sanitation and hygiene, and protection needs of the Gatumba humanitarian crisis in a bid to improve the living conditions of displaced flood-affected households in Bujumbura Rural and Bujumbura Mairie provinces.</narrative>
  </description>
